Human mobility modeling. It is useful to capture the general trend of mobility through simple mathematical expressions so that they can be easily integrated within the epidemiological model. Here, we introduce a simple ansatz for the global and local mobility. The early phases of the outbreak are characterized by a smooth mobility transition from the initial baseline mobility to a reduced mobility induced by behavioral changes in the population. Previously, we have modeled this transition by a hyperbolic tangent-type ansatz (Linka et al. 2020). Here, we generalize this approach by taking into account policy relaxations and social adaptations through a combination of exponentials,5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
