				\begin{document}$$\varDelta I(t,\varvec{\theta })$$\end{document}ΔI(t,θ) of our SEIR model. Arguably, the “date of reporting” can mean different things for different countries, and it can vary hugely between infection, symptom onset, testing, positive confirmed, and reporting. This implies that our time delay between mobility and reproduction is highly sensitive to the local testing logistics.Table 3
