Table 3 illustrates difference between symptom onset and reporting for four representative countries (European Center for Disease Prevention and Control 2020). For example, in Germany, the “date of reporting” represents the date at which a sample swab is sent to laboratory testing, although the actual date at which authorities are notified will be several days later. To illustrate the difference between symptom onset and reporting, we perform the same SEIR model analysis based on two different reported data sets \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
